      <title>Youngest Egyptian mummified fetus identified in British museum</title>
      <description>A computerized tomography scan of a small decorated Egyptian coffin has revealed the remains of a fetus that was just 16 to 18 weeks along, the Fitzwilliam Museum in Cambridge, England, has announced.</description>

      <title>Nefertiti still missing: King Tut's tomb shows no hidden chambers</title>
